    "notes": "Detection focus: (1) file.extension of .locked / .enc / .crypt / .crypted written by a non-system, non-backup process; (2) ransom note filename patterns (HOW_TO*, DECRYPT*, RESTORE_FILES*) created by the same process writing encrypted files; (3) process spawned from C:\\ProgramData\\ with embedded hex key arguments and powershell.exe as parent — ProgramData is not a normal parent directory for update binaries. Correlate process.pid across EID-1 and EID-11 events to link the process create to bulk file creation activity. Benign differentiators: trusted signed binaries (OneDrive, Defender) in versioned platform paths spawned by services.exe or known sync agents."
